---
import Page from "../layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page title="Projects" description="My current and past projects">
  <header class="mb-6 lg:mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-jlp-burnt">Projects</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="prose prose-sm sm:prose-base lg:prose-lg max-w-none">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-jlp-burnt">
        <a href="http://lunastationquarterly.com/" class="hover:text-jlp-burnt-light transition-colors">Luna Station Quarterly</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base">A labor of love, this is a quarterly magazine of genre fiction, written by women. I edit, design, and general handle all aspects of the production.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-jlp-burnt">
        <a href="http://lunastationpress.com/" class="hover:text-jlp-burnt-light transition-colors">Luna Station Press</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base">I'm the founder and publisher of this micro (boutique? personal? tiny?) independent publishing company. All of my work is published by LSP, along with the work of my dear Tara Quinn Lindsey and Elizabeth Hinckley and a few of our dear friends.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-jlp-burnt">
        <a href="https://www.woolgathering.xyz" class="hover:text-jlp-burnt-light transition-colors">Woolgathering</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base">
        I keep a public notebook of sorts, featuring resources on various tech and productivity topics. I've also written <a href="https://www.woolgathering.xyz/Writing/Fiction Writing Guide" class="hover:text-jlp-burnt-light transition-colors">a short guide to fiction writing</a>, focused on how I got started.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-jlp-burnt">
        <a href="http://readingdiet.tumblr.com/" class="hover:text-jlp-burnt-light transition-colors">Uncle Ray's Reading Diet</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base">A project that ran from August 13, 2009 to August 13, 2010. I read a short story, an essay, and a poem every single day for all 365 days.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Page>
